We have an app that use ml-kit to scan QR code.
There is issue when scan printed QR code they are not detected. But we are able to scan the original QR code image.
Just comparing with iOS with it's built-in camera feature, they are able to scan the printed QR code

**To Reproduce**
Example Steps to reproduce the behavior in sample app:
Go to 'Run the MLKit quickstart written in kotlin'
Click on 'LivePreviewActivity or CameraXLivePreviewActivity'
Select 'Barcode scanning' from the options
Scan printed QR code [here](https://imgur.com/a/NFjhjhP).
Observe, the QR code is not detected.

Click setting icon
Select 'rear camera preview size' from the options
Set to the highest size
Scan printed QR code [here](https://imgur.com/a/NFjhjhP).
Observe, the QR code is not detected.

Original QR code [here](https://imgur.com/a/7JxXhDo). download and use image preview to scan

**Expected behavior**
The scanned QR code should be detected

**SDK Info:**
 - SDK Name & Version [com.google.mlkit:barcode-scanning:17.0.2]

We are developing an app to scan Covid certificate QRCodes. EU, NZ QRCodes works great. ✔️

With Australia QRCodes, I'm having trouble detecting QR codes on any device. These QRCodes are dense compared to NZ and EU. I'm using CameraX and I tried multiple different configurations

- Set Target resolution for ImageAnalysis use case. If I set it to 1980X1080, it works randomly when I move back and forth.
- Continuos focus and metering
- Downgraded cameraX libraries from 1.1.0-beta to 1.0.2

**To Reproduce**

Steps to reproduce the behaviour in the sample app:
1. Go to 'Run the MLKit quickstart written in kotlin'
2. Click on 'LivePreviewActivity or CameraXLivePreviewActivity'
3. Select 'Barcode scanning' from the options
4. Scan barcodes named **Aus_*** from [here](https://github.com/harsha973/BarcodePlayground/tree/feature/issue_stack/sample_barcodes). 
5. Observe, the barcode is not detected.

Please also see my [barcode demo app](https://github.com/harsha973/BarcodePlayground/tree/feature/issue_stack). Please see MLKitActivity in the demo. Steps as below

1. Run the app
2. Click on 'MLKit' button
3. Scan barcode
4. Scan result doesn't show in the bottom white display area

**Expected behaviour**
The scanned barcode should be detected

**SDK Info:**
 - SDK Name & Version - com.google.mlkit:barcode-scanning:17.0.2
 - CameraX - androidx.camera:camera-lifecycle:1.1.0-beta01, androidx.camera:camera-view:1.1.0-beta01 androidx.camera:camera-camera2:1.1.0-beta01. Also tried with camera 1.0.2

**Smartphone:**
 - Device: Pixel 3, Android API 31
 - Device: Nokia 6.1, Android API 29

Please find the recorded [video](https://vimeo.com/manage/videos/677921037)

It's not a new change and should not take critical time, but there may be chance I guess that if your app recently does more stuff in the new release and then accumulating this ML Kit  initialization one might reach the ANR boundary on some devices?

To mitigate & verify this, you can remove the ML Kit auto-initialization and do it manually by this [MlKit#initialize](https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/mlkit/common/MlKit#public-static-void-initialize-context-context) call. You can call this on either UI thread (after startup for sure) or background thread, but please make sure the call is finished before you create a BarcodeScanner instance.
